    <h2>Best Practices to Generate Realistic Handwriting</h2>
    <p>Want your AI-generated handwriting to look as authentic as possible? Follow these proven tips:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Choose a Natural Style:</strong> Avoid overly perfect fonts. Pick styles with slight imperfections and natural curves.</li>
      <li><strong>Use a Lined Paper Background:</strong> A ruled paper background makes the output look instantly more authentic.</li>
      <li><strong>Add a Subtle Tilt:</strong> A very slight rotation of the text gives the impression of real human writing.</li>
      <li><strong>Use Blue or Black Ink:</strong> These are the most natural and credible colors for pen writing.</li>
      <li><strong>Add Proper Margins:</strong> Real notebooks always have margins — make sure your output includes them too.</li>
      <li><strong>Keep Paragraphs Short:</strong> Shorter blocks of text look more natural and readable in handwritten format.</li>
      <li><strong>Allow Letter Imperfections:</strong> Slight inconsistencies in individual letters make handwriting look more genuine.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Limitations of AI Handwriting</h2>
    <p>While <strong>AI handwriting generators</strong> are powerful, it is important to know their limitations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Not Truly Unique:</strong> AI cannot fully replicate a specific individual's handwriting style or personal signature.</li>
      <li><strong>Language Limitations:</strong> Many tools only support English or a limited number of languages.</li>
      <li><strong>Academic Integrity:</strong> Submitting AI-generated handwriting may violate some school or university policies — always check first.</li>
      <li><strong>Complex Symbols:</strong> Tools may struggle with math equations, chemical formulas, or non-Latin scripts.</li>
      <li><strong>Quality Varies:</strong> Free tools may have more limitations compared to premium paid versions.</li>
      <li><strong>No Emotional Depth:</strong> Real handwriting can subtly express emotion through pressure and stroke — AI cannot replicate this fully.</li>
    </ul>

